subSubSection.paragraph:
Female.
Differs from the male in clypeal punctation transverse, rough, and confluent; clypeal carina well defined and gradually tapering towards the genae. Genal sutures weakly impressed; clypeus subtrapezoidal, weakly elongate and sinuate apically; pronotal prominence reduced. Posterior tubercles located in the anterior portion of pronotum (
Fig. 15
). Ventral sclerotization of the sclerites: central-superior region with a convex superior margin; lateral-inferior regions projected outwards. Infundibulum: tubular region hook shaped; medial region well developed; caudal region weakly developed (
Fig. 16
).
